project.name: Driver Log Domain IPC3 SimpleTime
project.description:
This model was based on the SimpleTime version of the DriverLog domain from IPC-3 (2002)
This domain involves driving trucks around delivering packages between locations. The complication is that the trucks require drivers who must walk between trucks in order to drive them. The paths for walking and the roads for driving form different maps on the locations.
SimpleTime: Action durations vary from 20 for walking to 1 for simple boarding and disembarking. Concurrency is possible by using drivers and trucks in parallel, including both movement and loading or unloading activity.

actor.name: Truck
actor.description: This agent is responsible for transporting packages from a location to a another.

actor.name: Driver
actor.description: This agent is responsible for driving the trucks, and can also walk from a location to another.

useCase.name: Load a package
useCase.description: A package is loaded in the agent truck at a location.

definition.precondition: - the truck and the package must be at the same location; - there must be a driver driving the truck, i. e., it must not be empty.

useCase.name: Unload a package
useCase.description: A package is unloaded from the truck at a location.

useCase.name: Drive a truck
useCase.description: The agent driver drives a truck from an origin location to a destination location.

definition.invariants: - the driver remains driving the truck; - the truck load remains the same.

useCase.name: Board in a truck
useCase.description: The agent driver board in a truck at a location.

definition.precondition: - the truck and the driver must be at the same location; - the truck must be empty, i. e., without a driver.
definition.postcondition: - the driver is not at the location any more; - the driver is driving the truck.
definition.invariants: - the truck remains at the same location; - the truck load remains the same.

useCase.name: Disembark from a truck
useCase.description: The agent driver disembarck from a truck at a location.

definition.precondition: - the truck must be at the location; - the driver must be driving the truck.
definition.invariants: - the truck remains at the same location; - the truck load remains the same.

useCase.name: Walk
useCase.description: The agent driver walks from a origin location to a destination location.

definition.precondition: - the driver must be at the origin location; - there must be a path between the origin and the destination location.
definition.postcondition: - the driver is at the destination location; - the walked time is increased accordinglyn to the time to walk between the two locations.
definition.invariants: - the driver does not board in a truck while walking.
